  "texts": [
    "The first interesting physical observation here is that a q-dimensional operator in twisted sector for a (q + 1)-dimensional condensation defect can always be converted into a q-dimensional untwisted sector operator.",
    "This is because a condensation defect always admits a topological end, which allows us to perform the above transition as explained in figure 22.",
    "There might be multiple such topological ends and hence multiple ways of performing the above transition.",
    "However, one should note that there is a canonical topological end as well corresponding to Dirichlet boundary conditions for the gauge fields localized on the (q + 1)-dimensional locus occupied by the condensation defect.",
    "Below we assume that we have performed this transition using this canonical boundary condition."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}